WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.520 --> 00:00:05.540
A lot of people have this problem where their anger

2
00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:08.380
seems to come from nowhere. They feel fine one minute,

3
00:00:08.520 --> 00:00:10.620
and the next, they say or do something that they'll

4
00:00:10.660 --> 00:00:13.910
regret. For other people, this problem's even worse. It feels

5
00:00:13.940 --> 00:00:15.760
like they go from zero to one hundred in an

6
00:00:15.840 --> 00:00:19.940
instant. They go ballistic. But the reality is, anger doesn't

7
00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:23.860
come from nowhere. Anger starts small, and it grows gradually.

8
00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:27.220
But when anger is small, it tends to be hard

9
00:00:27.280 --> 00:00:30.220
to notice. Here's the good news. Even if you don't

10
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:33.740
consciously notice your anger starting to grow, your body still

11
00:00:33.780 --> 00:00:36.370
reacts. You might start to sweat a little bit. Your

12
00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:38.840
face might turn red. You might raise your voice a

13
00:00:38.940 --> 00:00:43.000
few decibels without even realizing it. We call these reactions

14
00:00:43.120 --> 00:00:46.340
anger warning signs. With a little bit of practice, you

15
00:00:46.380 --> 00:00:49.000
can learn to use these warning signs to your advantage

16
00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:52.400
to stop anger in its tracks. Let me tell you

17
00:00:52.460 --> 00:00:55.180
how. I like to think of anger warning signs in

18
00:00:55.260 --> 00:00:59.480
three categories: actions, physical symptoms, and thoughts.

19
00:01:00.510 --> 00:01:03.720
Action warning signs are anything that you do differently as

20
00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:06.150
your anger is starting to grow. For example, you might

21
00:01:06.160 --> 00:01:09.070
become argumentative or raise your voice, or maybe just the

22
00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:11.760
opposite. Maybe you lower your voice, look at your feet,

23
00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:14.990
as if you're trying to avoid confrontation. Physical symptoms are

24
00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:17.940
changes that happen to your body outside of your control,

25
00:01:18.380 --> 00:01:23.300
for example, sweating, shaking, turning red, feeling hot, or shallow

26
00:01:23.340 --> 00:01:28.050
breathing. Finally, thoughts. These warning signs include changes to the

27
00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:30.380
way that you think as your anger is starting to

28
00:01:30.400 --> 00:01:33.800
grow. For example, you might become really fixated on the

29
00:01:33.820 --> 00:01:37.020
source of your anger, or maybe particular thoughts go through

30
00:01:37.040 --> 00:01:41.620
your head, like, "I've been disrespected," or, "This is unfair."

31
00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:45.790
Now, everyone has their own personal warning signs. You might

32
00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:49.170
relate with something that I've just described, or you might

33
00:01:49.200 --> 00:01:52.930
experience something that's completely unique and personal to you. One

34
00:01:52.960 --> 00:01:54.830
of the best ways to learn about your own anger

35
00:01:54.920 --> 00:01:57.940
warning signs is with an anger thermometer. You can do

36
00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:00.400
this on a worksheet or a blank sheet of paper.

37
00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:03.190
To begin, write the number ten at the top of

38
00:02:03.220 --> 00:02:06.260
the paper and number down to one, leaving a few

39
00:02:06.320 --> 00:02:11.009
blank lines after each number. Next, imagine your anger on

40
00:02:11.060 --> 00:02:14.500
a ten-point scale. A ten is the angriest you've ever

41
00:02:14.540 --> 00:02:18.660
been, while a one is completely calm. Think of a

42
00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:21.840
time when your anger was at a ten. What were

43
00:02:21.850 --> 00:02:25.420
your anger warning signs in that moment? Maybe you became

44
00:02:25.480 --> 00:02:29.180
argumentative or physically aggressive, or maybe your body shook with

45
00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:32.300
rage. Whatever it was, write it down. Try to think

46
00:02:32.340 --> 00:02:36.910
of all three categories: actions, physical symptoms, and

47
00:02:36.920 --> 00:02:40.300
thoughts. Now, go down to the bottom. What are you

48
00:02:40.340 --> 00:02:43.320
like at a one on the scale? Maybe you're friendly,

49
00:02:43.420 --> 00:02:48.240
relaxed, or agreeable. Whatever it is, write it down. Next,

50
00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:51.470
go to the middle, a five on the scale. At

51
00:02:51.500 --> 00:02:54.120
this point, you aren't calm, but you're still a pretty

52
00:02:54.160 --> 00:02:56.980
long ways from a ten. Write down the anger warning

53
00:02:57.060 --> 00:03:00.260
signs that you have at this point. And finally, let's

54
00:03:00.269 --> 00:03:02.859
try to fill in a few blanks along the scale.

55
00:03:02.880 --> 00:03:05.100
For example, maybe you know when you're just starting to

56
00:03:05.120 --> 00:03:08.280
get frustrated, you sort of tap your foot, maybe at

57
00:03:08.320 --> 00:03:11.680
a three. Write that down, along with any other warning

58
00:03:11.700 --> 00:03:14.010
signs that you can think of. Now, all of these

59
00:03:14.060 --> 00:03:17.870
items, these are your anger warning signs. The items at

60
00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:21.609
the bottom of your thermometer, they're especially valuable because they're

61
00:03:21.620 --> 00:03:24.900
gonna give you the most advanced warning that your anger

62
00:03:24.940 --> 00:03:27.600
is starting to develop. Once you've learned to catch your

63
00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:30.870
anger early, it becomes much easier to control. You can

64
00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:34.780
come at situations rationally rather than emotionally. That means you

65
00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:38.720
can put yourself on warning, use a relaxation skill, or

66
00:03:38.800 --> 00:03:42.020
just walk away if that's what it takes. Now, catching

67
00:03:42.040 --> 00:03:44.480
your anger warning signs in the moment won't be easy

68
00:03:44.520 --> 00:03:48.100
at first. It takes practice. So to start, you should

69
00:03:48.140 --> 00:03:51.260
review your anger thermometer every day just to keep those

70
00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:54.200
warning signs fresh in your mind. And if you do

71
00:03:54.240 --> 00:03:56.549
have a slip-up where you have an angry episode that

72
00:03:56.560 --> 00:03:59.630
you don't catch in time, that's okay. But use it

73
00:03:59.680 --> 00:04:02.870
as a learning opportunity. The next day, take a look

74
00:04:02.960 --> 00:04:06.510
back and ask yourself, "What clues did I miss?" Now,

75
00:04:06.820 --> 00:04:09.690
with practice, you will learn to catch your anger early,

76
00:04:10.020 --> 00:04:12.280
and this is gonna put the power back in your

77
00:04:12.340 --> 00:04:12.700
hands.
